namespace Java.Util

Contains .NET proxy types for Java classes from the package java.util.

See:
          Description

Type Summary
AbstractCollection .NET proxy type for class java.util.AbstractCollection.
This class provides a skeletal implementation of the Collection interface, to minimize the effort required to implement this interface.
AbstractList .NET proxy type for class java.util.AbstractList.
This class provides a skeletal implementation of the Java.Util.List interface to minimize the effort required to implement this interface backed by a "random access" data store (such as an array).
Calendar .NET proxy type for class java.util.Calendar.
The Calendar class is an abstract class that provides methods for converting between a specific instant in time and a set of .fields such as YEAR, MONTH, DAY_OF_MONTH, HOUR, and so on, and for manipulating the calendar fields, such as getting the date of the next week.
Collection .NET proxy type for interface java.util.Collection.
Comparator .NET proxy type for interface java.util.Comparator.
Date .NET proxy type for class java.util.Date.
The class Date represents a specific instant in time, with millisecond precision.
Dictionary .NET proxy type for class java.util.Dictionary.
The Dictionary class is the abstract parent of any class, such as Hashtable, which maps keys to values.
Enumeration .NET proxy type for interface java.util.Enumeration.
An object that implements the Enumeration interface generates a series of elements, one at a time.
EventListener .NET proxy type for interface java.util.EventListener.
A tagging interface that all event listener interfaces must extend.
EventObject .NET proxy type for class java.util.EventObject.
The root class from which all event state objects shall be derived.
Hashtable .NET proxy type for class java.util.Hashtable.
This class implements a hash table, which maps keys to values.
Iterator .NET proxy type for interface java.util.Iterator.
List .NET proxy type for interface java.util.List.
ListIterator .NET proxy type for interface java.util.ListIterator.
An iterator for lists that allows the programmer to traverse the list in either direction, modify the list during iteration, and obtain the iterator's current position in the list.
Map .NET proxy type for interface java.util.Map.
Properties .NET proxy type for class java.util.Properties.
The Properties class represents a persistent set of properties.
RandomAccess .NET proxy type for interface java.util.RandomAccess.
Marker interface used by List implementations to indicate that they support fast (generally constant time) random access.
Spliterator .NET proxy type for interface java.util.Spliterator.
Vector .NET proxy type for class java.util.Vector.
The Vector class implements a growable array of objects.
